> =20
> Good morning, Raffaella.
> =20
> I hope you are well this morning.
> =20
> You will receive the $9,000 temporary accommodation payment in 3 to 5 =
working days.
> =20
> The remaining amount under the temporary accommodation benefit is =
$13,820.62
> =20
> Is there a time I can contact you this week by phone to finalize your =
contents claim? the loss schedule provided by Asset Restore to date =
exceeds your sum insured, which means that the contents is a total loss =
as the total value of the contents damaged or destroyed is greater then =
the sum insured. I work until 1:30 so let me know when this week suits =
you.
> =20
> I have confirmation that your privacy request and the information you =
requested was emailed to you on the 25/07/25. If you can check this date =
and let me know if you have it.
> =20
> Regarding updates, I am more then happy to update you on the first of =
each month, would you prefer monthly contacts from me instead of =
fortnightly?
> =20
> Regarding further claim files, we can send you assessor reports as we =
receive these from the assessor. It would be less prudent for us to =
resend you the entire claim file each month and not efficient for us due =
to the time it takes to action these we may end up getting assessor =
reports during this process which means that report may not be added to =
that privacy request.
> =20
> Future assessor reports should be the only documents we have that you =
are not given by the assessor as this would come from us.
> =20
> Kind regards,
> =20
> Zach
